K4 & Kindergarten registration for the ECLC is open! To begin the process, go to the district website enrollment tab: https://www.gorockets.org/EnrollinginTitusvilleAreaSchoolDistrict.aspx

After you choose an appointment time, send required documents in an email to: tasd.covid-19@gorockets.org. Required documents: child's birth certificate, photo ID of person enrolling the child, proof of your residency (a deed. current utility bill with address, vehicle registration, or DOT ID card.)
Once your documents are received, a registrar will contact you to confirm the information. If you are unable to complete registration online, call 827-2715 ext. 8-3400.

County-wide telephone "warm line" to assist families during COVID-19. Call 814-724-1116 or 833-491-4673 (toll-free).
Call seven days a week between 9:00 a.m. and 9:00 p.m.
This call line is not for emergencies. Calls are being triaged by Women's Services Hotline staff and referred to one of over 40 trained volunteers willing to help individuals work through non-emergency challenges as a result of impact of COVID-19.

Over the next few weeks, our teachers will be working to provide more targeted review and enrichment resources for our students. We will start sharing soon. Until then, we hope that you and your child find these resources useful.

The Governor extended the mandated school closure through Monday, April 6, 2020. We are working hard to provide instructional materials to parents for use at home with your children. Some of the lessons may be online and some may be in the form of paper packets. The building principals will soon be sharing this information by the end of this week.

Please continue to follow PA Dept. of Health recommendations for social distancing as this is our best chance at being able to get back to school sooner.

post_text: MEALS: Now three (3) pick up locations: Pleasantville Elementary, Hydetown Elementary and Titusville Middle School. Bag lunch and bag breakfast meals are available for students during the school closure 11:00 a.m. until 12:30 p.m. Each student receiving meals must be physically present in the vehicle, as required by state guidelines. Any child in the school district, age 18 or younger, is eligible even if they do not attend any of our schools. On Friday, 3 meals will be provided for the weekend.
text: MEALS: Now three (3) pick up locations: Pleasantville Elementary, Hydetown Elementary and Titusville Middle School. Bag lunch and bag breakfast meals are available for students during the school closure 11:00 a.m. until 12:30 p.m. Each student receiving meals must be physically present in the vehicle, as required by state guidelines. Any child in the school district, age 18 or younger, is eligible even if they do not attend any of our schools. On Friday, 3 meals will be provided for the weekend.

post_text:
The district will be providing bag lunch and bag breakfast meals for students during the school closure. These meals will be distributed using a drive-through approach, so families do not need to get out of their vehicle. Meals will be distributed from the Titusville Middle School bus loop at the back of the building each day from 11:00 a.m. until 12:30 p.m.
Students must be in the vehicle when picking up meals, in order to follow state guidelines. Each student receiving a lunch and breakfast must be physically present in the vehicle. Any child in the school district, age 18 or younger is eligible to receive the food even if they do not attend any of our schools.

post_text: The TASD Athletic Department is excited to announce that we are now offering the convenience of online athletic registration through FamilyID (www.familyid.com). When you register through FamilyID, the system keeps track of your information in your FamilyID profile. You enter your information only once for each family member for multiple uses and multiple programs. Registration is now open for Fall athletics for both the middle school and the high school. Registration for Winter and Spring sports will be available soon. Any question, please contact the athletic office at 814-827-2715 ext. 1440 or 1443.

Care you can trust for all acute and chronic illnesses.
The office will treat patients of all ages.
• Medical appointments and lab draws will be available
Monday, Wednesday and Friday.
• Beginning April 1, call 814-755-3631 to establish as a patient.

Appointments will not be necessary for blood work.
• Most insurances including Medicare, Medicaid and
commercial insurances will be accepted.

The Titusville High School Varsity Club will be holding their annual pasta dinner tomorrow evening Tuesday March, 19, 2019 from 4:30-6:30 pm in the Titusville High School cafeteria.
Tickets can be purchased at the door at a cost of $8.00.
The menu will include pasta, meatballs, tossed salad, bread sticks, and ice cream.
Pasta without meatballs will be available for those observing lent.
Takeout is available.
Thank you for your support.

post_text:
The Titusville Rockets Baseball Team will host a chicken and biscuit fundraising dinner at the Titusville Moose Lodge, this Saturday, January 26, from 1:00 p.m. to 5:00 p.m. This fundraiser will help aid the Titusville Rocket Baseball team's spring training trip to Florida.

The chicken and biscuit dinner will include mashed potatoes, peas & carrots, along with apple sauce and dessert. Take-outs are also available and walk-ins are always welcome.

Cost of the dinner is $8.00 per ticket and can be purchased from any Rocket Baseball Player, Parent, or Coach and directly from The Titusville Moose Lodge.

Please come out this Saturday, and help support our Titusville Rockets Baseball Team.

post_text:
THS great news coming out of District Band!
Josh Devlin took first chair for the baritone saxes and will be moving on to Region Band. Wyatt Duncan took 3rd chair for tuba and will be moving on to Region Band. Xavian Sider took 1st chair on first French Horn and will be moving on to Region Band. Abigail Vinson took 2nd chair on second clarinet and will be moving on to Region Band. Lindsay Sines had a great audition, but just missed moving on by one chair.
We congratulate them on their outstanding performance! If you are free this Saturday 1/26/19, the Region Band concert is at Meadville High School at 1 PM. We would love to have lots of support for our students!
